00:28:28.220 --> 00:28:33.900
parent, a pastor. No, walk worthy of God, and guess what? You can deceive a teacher

00:28:33.900 --> 00:28:41.660
a parent, a pastor, but you can't deceive God. It's impossible. And so this process

00:28:41.660 --> 00:28:47.940
of examination, listen, you've spent so much time examining the Apostle Paul, how

00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:52.619
about you examine yourself? You ever been in a situation where you feel like you're

00:28:52.619 --> 00:28:59.580
under the microscope? People often speak, and I don't say this in a pity kind

00:28:59.580 --> 00:29:03.260
of a way, just something that's been, there's actually been books written with

00:29:03.260 --> 00:29:07.059
this kind of a title, is living in a fishbowl. They talk about people that are

00:29:07.059 --> 00:29:10.540
spiritual leaders, and you kind of live in a fishbowl, a fish tank, where

00:29:10.540 --> 00:29:15.380
everyone's always looking at you, and always looking at you, and I get it. If

00:29:15.380 --> 00:29:21.540
you're in any place of leadership, that often is the case, but I want you to

00:29:21.540 --> 00:29:24.740
understand that as they were examining the Apostle Paul, and Paul wasn't really

00:29:24.740 --> 00:29:27.940
too concerned about them examining him, but he said, listen, you need to examine

00:29:27.940 --> 00:29:32.140
yourselves. You know why Paul, I think, really didn't, it didn't affect him

00:29:32.180 --> 00:29:35.980
greatly that they were putting him under the microscope, because Paul put

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:41.900
himself under the microscope. See, Paul examined himself, so if someone else was

00:29:41.900 --> 00:29:45.300
going to come in and examine him, it really didn't affect him too much, it

00:29:45.300 --> 00:29:48.740
didn't bother him too much. Why? Because he had already examined himself, he'd

00:29:48.740 --> 00:29:52.860
already got along with God, he already had lived in seeking to please the Lord

00:29:52.860 --> 00:29:56.860
with his life, and he wanted to live a life, in fact, he says it this way in Acts

00:29:56.860 --> 00:30:02.020
24 and verse 16, and herein do I exercise myself...

00:30:02.020 --> 00:30:04.900
to have always a conscience void of offense

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:07.460
toward God and toward men.

00:30:07.460 --> 00:30:09.840
And so the Apostle Paul lived that way,

00:30:09.840 --> 00:30:11.340
but he's saying to these believers in Corinth,

00:30:11.340 --> 00:30:15.980
stop examining me, examine yourselves.

00:30:15.980 --> 00:30:18.380
Whether you be in the faith, prove your own selves,

00:30:18.380 --> 00:30:21.280
know your own selves, how that Jesus Christ is in you.

00:30:21.280 --> 00:30:24.100
Aren't you thankful, Christ in me, the hope of glory.

00:30:24.100 --> 00:30:25.620
Listen, when you got saved, the Bible tells us

00:30:25.620 --> 00:30:28.620
the Holy Spirit of God indwelled you at that moment.

00:30:28.620 --> 00:30:30.920
You're sealed unto the day of redemption

00:30:30.920 --> 00:30:34.920
with the Holy Spirit, and what a joy, and what a blessing.

00:30:34.920 --> 00:30:37.840
And you need to know that you know that you know

00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:39.360
that heaven is your home.

00:30:40.320 --> 00:30:44.640
Examine yourselves, whether you be in the faith.

00:30:44.640 --> 00:30:48.440
And so Paul gives this demand to these believers

00:30:48.440 --> 00:30:50.900
here in Corinth, he reminds them,

00:30:50.900 --> 00:30:52.800
but then he gives to them a demand.

00:30:52.800 --> 00:30:55.440
He says in verse six, but I trust that you shall know

00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:57.000
that we are not reprobates.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:59.840
You know, I believe that what Paul's kind of hinting

00:30:59.840 --> 00:31:02.680
towards here in verse number six, you've examined me

00:31:02.680 --> 00:31:04.880
and you're probably gonna keep examining me

00:31:04.880 --> 00:31:07.960
and you're gonna find out that I passed the test.

00:31:07.960 --> 00:31:10.480
Not pridefully, not arrogantly, listen,

00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:12.480
I'm not saved because of anything I've done,

00:31:12.480 --> 00:31:16.000
I'm saved because Jesus Christ saved this lost sinner.

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:17.000
Amen?

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:19.900
And so when he's talking about being in the faith

00:31:19.900 --> 00:31:23.240
and having the truth of being born again,

00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:25.320
Paul says, listen, I know you've examined me,

00:31:25.320 --> 00:31:26.800
I know you're gonna keep examining me,

00:31:26.800 --> 00:31:29.440
but you're gonna know that we are not reprobates.

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:31.400
We have passed the test.

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:35.400
Then I want you to notice the concern.

00:31:35.400 --> 00:31:37.780
As we wrap up in verses seven through 10,

00:31:37.780 --> 00:31:41.140
the Apostle Paul once again is going to share his heart

00:31:41.140 --> 00:31:43.560
with these believers in Corinth and really his heart

00:31:43.560 --> 00:31:45.840
for the believers in Corinth.

00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:48.340
And we find the concern of the Apostle Paul

00:31:48.340 --> 00:31:50.640
in verse number seven and eight, he's concerned

00:31:50.640 --> 00:31:52.440
for their deeds, for their actions,

00:31:52.440 --> 00:31:53.480
for those things that they do.

00:31:53.480 --> 00:31:55.420
Notice in verse number seven, he says,

00:31:55.420 --> 00:32:00.420
now I pray to God that ye do no evil.

00:32:02.700 --> 00:32:06.060
He had mentioned in verses 20 and 21 of chapter 12

00:32:06.060 --> 00:32:09.340
about the dealing with sin, that sin must be addressed.

00:32:09.340 --> 00:32:12.300
He mentioned in verse number two about those that have sinned

00:32:12.300 --> 00:32:15.240
and we find here that he says that I pray to God

00:32:15.240 --> 00:32:17.340
that ye do no evil.

00:32:17.340 --> 00:32:20.060
You know, this is a concern that the Apostle Paul has

00:32:20.060 --> 00:32:23.340
for these believers in Corinth, those that are born again,

00:32:23.380 --> 00:32:24.300
those that are saved.

00:32:24.300 --> 00:32:28.780
Listen, my desire, our desire is that you would walk worthy,

00:32:28.780 --> 00:32:30.900
that you would do no evil.

00:32:30.900 --> 00:32:32.820
Notice he continues in verse number seven,

00:32:32.820 --> 00:32:34.660
not that we should appear approved,

00:32:34.660 --> 00:32:37.900
but that we should do that which is honest,

00:32:37.900 --> 00:32:39.340
though we be as reprobates.

00:32:39.340 --> 00:32:42.860
He's saying not only concerning their deeds to do no evil,

00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:45.000
but to do that which is honest.

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.340
You know, Christians ought to be honest people.

00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:49.340
Amen?

00:32:50.340 --> 00:32:53.180
I mean, how terrible.

00:32:53.180 --> 00:32:55.340
I understand that we live in a society

00:32:55.340 --> 00:32:57.500
in which honesty and transparency

00:32:57.500 --> 00:33:00.300
is not the norm any longer.

00:33:00.300 --> 00:33:02.640
I know I've never lived in the days,

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:04.360
but I've heard about people

00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:07.800
that made huge agreements on handshakes.

00:33:09.100 --> 00:33:11.140
Transactions that were done,

00:33:11.140 --> 00:33:14.260
business transactions on handshakes.

00:33:14.260 --> 00:33:17.100
And now we have documents that are pages,

00:33:17.100 --> 00:33:20.020
dozens and hundreds of pages long,

00:33:20.020 --> 00:33:22.420
and lawyers involved on all sides,

00:33:22.420 --> 00:33:23.900
and all of those types of things.

00:33:23.900 --> 00:33:25.620
And listen, there was a day and age

00:33:25.620 --> 00:33:29.280
in which honesty was appreciated

00:33:29.280 --> 00:33:32.920
and was something that was really looked up to.

00:33:35.820 --> 00:33:37.820
That you should do that which is honest.

00:33:37.820 --> 00:33:39.740
You know, Paul says to the believers in Philippi,

00:33:39.740 --> 00:33:42.260
I mentioned last week about the put off

00:33:42.260 --> 00:33:43.900
and put on principle,

00:33:43.900 --> 00:33:47.220
and the fact that we're to walk worthy.

00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:49.580
And Paul said this to those,

00:33:49.580 --> 00:33:51.860
I think I said Philippi, Ephesus,

00:33:51.860 --> 00:33:55.180
in Ephesians chapter number four, five, four.

00:33:55.180 --> 00:33:58.020
He tells them about the putting off and putting on,

00:33:58.020 --> 00:34:00.980
and he tells them this in verse 25 of Ephesians four,

00:34:00.980 --> 00:34:04.020
"'Wherefore, putting away lying.

00:34:04.020 --> 00:34:06.740
"'Speak every man truth with his neighbor,

00:34:06.740 --> 00:34:08.980
"'for we are members one of another.'"

00:34:10.260 --> 00:34:11.860
Putting away lying.

00:34:11.860 --> 00:34:16.340
So Paul says here, I pray to God that you do no evil,

00:34:16.340 --> 00:34:19.500
that you should do that which is honest.

00:34:19.500 --> 00:34:21.580
This is Paul's concern for their deeds,

00:34:21.580 --> 00:34:23.260
for their actions, for those things

00:34:23.260 --> 00:34:24.140
that they're going to do.

00:34:24.140 --> 00:34:26.260
But then as we transition here,

00:34:26.260 --> 00:34:27.500
notice he says in verse eight,

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:28.820
and we're gonna get back to verse number eight

00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:30.140
as we wrap the whole message up,

00:34:30.140 --> 00:34:30.980
but he says this,

00:34:30.980 --> 00:34:33.140
"'For we can do nothing against the truth,

00:34:33.140 --> 00:34:35.220
"'but for the truth.'"

00:34:35.220 --> 00:34:36.060
Can I tell you this morning,

00:34:36.060 --> 00:34:38.380
you're not gonna change God's mind.

00:34:38.380 --> 00:34:40.940
You're not gonna change God's truth.

00:34:40.940 --> 00:34:42.060
You're not going to.

00:34:42.060 --> 00:34:44.140
God's truth is settled.

00:34:44.140 --> 00:34:45.900
You're not gonna change it.

00:34:45.900 --> 00:34:46.860
In verse nine, it says,

00:34:46.860 --> 00:34:49.980
"'For we are glad when we are weak,

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:53.380
"'and you're strong in this also we wish,

00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:55.380
"'even your perfection.

00:34:55.380 --> 00:34:57.820
"'Therefore I write these things being absent,

00:34:57.820 --> 00:35:00.100
"'lest being present I should use sharpness,

00:35:00.100 --> 00:35:01.620
"'according to the power which the Lord

00:35:01.620 --> 00:35:05.180
"'hath given me to edification and not to destruction.'"

00:35:05.180 --> 00:35:07.460
So as we unpack verses nine and 10,

00:35:07.460 --> 00:35:09.740
I believe that Paul's concern here

00:35:09.740 --> 00:35:12.500
for the believers in Corinth is for their growth,

00:35:12.500 --> 00:35:14.020
their spiritual growth.

00:35:14.020 --> 00:35:16.340
He mentions again at the end of verse number 10

00:35:16.340 --> 00:35:18.780
about the power that God gave him,

00:35:18.780 --> 00:35:22.220
but that power was given to him for edification,

00:35:22.220 --> 00:35:24.260
to build up,

00:35:24.260 --> 00:35:28.780
to see somebody grow in their walk with Christ,

00:35:28.780 --> 00:35:30.340
not to destruction.

00:35:30.340 --> 00:35:33.340
We find that he mentions in verse number nine,

00:35:33.340 --> 00:35:34.380
notice at the end it says,

00:35:34.380 --> 00:35:37.580
"'In this also we wish,

00:35:37.580 --> 00:35:39.620
"'even your perfection.'"

00:35:40.460 --> 00:35:42.860
That word wish really carries with the idea of a prayer,

00:35:42.860 --> 00:35:45.940
this desire that Paul has for them,

00:35:45.940 --> 00:35:49.260
and as we think about the growth here,

00:35:49.260 --> 00:35:50.460
he says in verse number nine,

00:35:50.460 --> 00:35:53.300
"'Even your perfection.'"

00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:56.540
He says in verse number 10 about edification,

00:35:56.540 --> 00:36:00.820
and I begin to think about the two uses of these words here

00:36:00.820 --> 00:36:04.260
of that which is perfection and also the edification,

00:36:04.260 --> 00:36:06.860
and really what Paul is referencing here

00:36:06.860 --> 00:36:09.140
is for their spiritual maturity.

00:36:10.020 --> 00:36:11.780
That they would be equipped.

00:36:11.780 --> 00:36:13.940
The word perfection at the end of verse number nine

00:36:13.940 --> 00:36:15.780
is an interesting word.

00:36:16.660 --> 00:36:18.500
It's a word that was very familiar

00:36:18.500 --> 00:36:23.500
that was used in a multitude of scenarios.

00:36:23.580 --> 00:36:26.620
It was a word that these believers

00:36:26.620 --> 00:36:27.860
would be able to relate to

00:36:27.860 --> 00:36:32.780
in a number of different arenas of life, if you will.

00:36:32.780 --> 00:36:35.340
We understand that it's Bible, that it's scripture,

00:36:35.340 --> 00:36:37.740
that Paul is writing to these,

00:36:37.740 --> 00:36:39.980
and that he's concerned about their spiritual growth,

00:36:39.980 --> 00:36:42.460
their perfection, that spiritual maturity,

00:36:42.460 --> 00:36:45.100
but we find that the term, the same exact term,

00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:47.900
would be used within the medical field,

00:36:47.900 --> 00:36:49.040
and within the medical field,

00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:54.040
it would be used to have this idea of setting a broken bone.

00:36:56.500 --> 00:36:58.540
I don't know if you ever had a broken bone,

00:36:58.540 --> 00:37:01.380
and it needed to be set,

00:37:01.380 --> 00:37:04.860
and when I broke my pinky, it was a displaced fracture.

00:37:04.860 --> 00:37:06.820
They thought they were gonna have to do surgery.

00:37:06.820 --> 00:37:08.740
I really didn't want to have to have surgery,

00:37:08.740 --> 00:37:11.500
and they were able to get that thing to be corrected

00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:13.380
because it was a displaced fracture,

00:37:13.380 --> 00:37:14.780
but it had to be set.

00:37:14.780 --> 00:37:18.200
Thankfully, it wasn't too awfully painful

00:37:18.200 --> 00:37:19.220
going through that process,

00:37:19.220 --> 00:37:21.860
but I understand some people that have had broken bones,

00:37:21.860 --> 00:37:26.340
and they have to be set, it's a painful process.

00:37:27.180 --> 00:37:29.880
And so it means, within that medical use of the term,

00:37:29.880 --> 00:37:31.020
to set a broken bone,

00:37:31.020 --> 00:37:33.340
within the nautical world,

00:37:33.340 --> 00:37:36.620
it would mean to outfit a ship for voyage.

00:37:37.820 --> 00:37:40.300
And within military usage,

00:37:40.300 --> 00:37:43.940
it would mean to equip an army for battle.

00:37:43.940 --> 00:37:45.420
So you think about those usages,

00:37:45.420 --> 00:37:48.540
and again, it's a word that all of these folks

00:37:48.540 --> 00:37:50.740
could easily associate with and understand

00:37:50.740 --> 00:37:52.180
what Paul is saying to them

00:37:52.180 --> 00:37:56.980
when he says that this also we wish,

00:37:56.980 --> 00:38:01.860
even your perfection, your spiritual maturity,

00:38:01.860 --> 00:38:05.880
your equipping, the idea that Paul is concerned

00:38:05.920 --> 00:38:07.800
for them spiritually, why?

00:38:07.800 --> 00:38:10.840
Because he knows that they're gonna stand before Christ,

00:38:10.840 --> 00:38:13.080
and he's concerned for them.

00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:16.240
Why is it that Paul mentioned in chapter number 11,

00:38:16.240 --> 00:38:17.800
that which cometh upon me daily,

00:38:17.800 --> 00:38:19.440
the care of all the churches?

00:38:19.440 --> 00:38:22.280
Why did Paul care so much about the people

00:38:22.280 --> 00:38:24.640
that God had allowed him to minister to?

00:38:24.640 --> 00:38:26.160
Because he understood that those people

00:38:26.160 --> 00:38:28.720
were gonna stand before God one day,

00:38:28.720 --> 00:38:30.760
and he wanted them to walk worthy,

00:38:30.760 --> 00:38:32.400
he wanted them to please God,

00:38:32.400 --> 00:38:34.280
he wanted them to be able to stand

00:38:34.280 --> 00:38:36.280
and to give a good account.

00:38:37.200 --> 00:38:39.600
I think about what we read in the Gospels.

00:38:39.600 --> 00:38:42.700
Well done, thou good and faithful servant.

00:38:44.400 --> 00:38:48.160
And Paul is concerned about their spiritual maturity,

00:38:48.160 --> 00:38:51.160
and we ask ourselves the question this morning,

00:38:51.160 --> 00:38:54.679
how is it when we begin to think about this perfection

00:38:54.679 --> 00:38:56.820
and the spiritual maturity, what does it look like?

00:38:56.820 --> 00:38:59.440
How is it accomplished in the life of a believer?

00:38:59.440 --> 00:39:01.400
Look, if you will, at Hebrews chapter 13.

00:39:01.400 --> 00:39:02.720
We're gonna look at a few passages

00:39:02.720 --> 00:39:04.160
as we wrap up this morning,

00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:07.440
but I want you to consider this final really concern

00:39:07.440 --> 00:39:09.520
that Paul has for these believers.

00:39:09.520 --> 00:39:12.320
In Hebrews 13, we read about the same idea

00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:15.920
of this perfection and the work that God is doing in you.

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:19.200
I'm thankful for the song that we sing with the children.

00:39:19.200 --> 00:39:24.200
God's still working on me to make me what I ought to be.

00:39:25.220 --> 00:39:26.480
Aren't you thankful?

00:39:26.480 --> 00:39:28.660
Listen, when the Lord works in your life,

00:39:28.660 --> 00:39:30.619
when he's ministering to you,

00:39:30.619 --> 00:39:33.440
when he's using his word to grow you,

00:39:33.720 --> 00:39:36.320
we ought to rejoice in that.

00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:38.480
Can I say this, and I don't say this

00:39:38.480 --> 00:39:41.400
in order to try to manipulate some type of response,

00:39:41.400 --> 00:39:42.360
but can I say this?

00:39:42.360 --> 00:39:46.520
It's not a bad thing to visit an altar in a church.

00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:49.480
It's actually a good thing to visit an altar in a church.

00:39:49.480 --> 00:39:51.480
Somebody mentioned to me not long ago

00:39:51.480 --> 00:39:53.640
how that it was so perplexing to them

00:39:53.640 --> 00:39:55.760
because they've been in different parts of the world,

00:39:55.760 --> 00:39:57.920
